  <main class="main-content">
    <div class="page-header">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>How we protect and manage your data</p>
    </div>
    <div class="static-page-card">
      <p><strong>Last Updated: April 2026</strong></p>
      <p>At Community Help Hub, your privacy is our priority. We are committed to protecting your personal information and being completely transparent about how we use it.</p>
      <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
      <p>When you register for an account, we collect basic personal details such as your name, email address, general location, and the skills you choose to share on your profile. If you post a request, we collect the details of that request to show to potential volunteers.</p>
      <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
      <p>We use your data strictly to operate our platform and connect volunteers with those in need in their local area. Your email is used for account verification, password resets, and important service notifications. <strong>We do not sell your personal data to third-party marketing companies.</strong></p>
      <h3>3. Cookies and Tracking</h3>
      <p>Like most websites, we use basic cookies to keep you logged into your account and to remember your preferences. You can disable cookies in your browser, but some features may not function properly without them.</p>
      <h3>4. Data Protection</h3>
      <p>We use industry-standard security measures to keep your passwords and personal information safe from unauthorized access. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.</p>
      <h3>5. Your Rights</h3>
      <p>You have the right to access, edit, or permanently delete your account and personal data at any time from your Profile settings.</p>
      <h3>6. Contact Us</h3>
      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please reach out at <strong>support@communityhelpub.org</strong>.</p>
    </div>
